item.title: JAR issue Please help [317]
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Your “error” is because there is no command-line args.
Basically, it’s looking for something similar to:
30 0 highmem members 32
After where your jar debugger would call the .jar
so it’d be like:
yourjar.jar 30 0 highmem members 32

Usually, the client should have a default for all of those and it shouldn’t matter.

Read full topic
